#include <stdio.h>

int main() {

    int count = 1;

  printf("Counting from 1 to 5 using a do-while loop:\n");

 do {

        printf("%d\n", count);

        count++;

    } while (count <= 5);

    return 0;

}
In this program, we use a for loop to calculate the sum of numbers from 1 to a user-defined positive integer n. The for loop iterates through the numbers from 1 to n and accumulates their sum in the sum variable. 
